        <abbr>4.1.7.4</abbr>
        <gi>termOfRestriction</gi>
    </head>
    <div type="semanticcomponents">
        <!-- PREMIS Semantic components -->
        <p>4.1.7.4.1 startDate</p>
        <p>4.1.7.4.2 endDate</p>
    </div>
    <div type="definition">
        <!-- PREMIS Definition -->
        <p>The time period for the restriction granted.</p>
    </div>
    <div type="rationale">
        <!-- PREMIS Rationale -->
        <p>The current definition of <bold>termOfGrant</bold> is "time period for the
            permissions granted". This allows repositories to express information
            about the Rights granted, but some repositories may need to express
            time-bounded restrictions like embargoes. To express such restrictions,
            use the semantic units of termOfRestriction: <bold>startDate</bold> for the
            beginning of the embargo and <bold>endDate</bold> for the end of the
            embargo.</p>
    </div>
